parameters:
\N<Yuia>Segi, are you alright? You're not in someone else's body
anymore, so please don't push yourself too hard.

\N<Segi>I'm fine, really. Yuia-sama, you must be tired from
instructing the vigilante group, right?

\N<Yuia>That's nothing to worry about. I'm more concerned about your
health...

\N<Segi>I told you I'm fine. I'm surprisingly sturdy, you know. Have
I ever been bedridden before?

\N<Yuia>We've... really been through a lot, haven't we? There were
tragedies that made us want to look away, and sad events
we'd rather not remember.

\N<Yuia>I've wondered... what did I do to deserve this? There were
times when I thought this must be some kind of punishment.

\N<Yuia>But... I want to put an end to such struggles and self-
blame. No... I'm sure I can put an end to it.

\N<Yuia>From now on... things will surely get better. This child
will become the symbol of our future.

\N<Yuia>We've tasted enough bitterness up until now. So from here on
out, it would be a lie if fate didn't take a turn for the
better, don't you think?
\N<Segi>...Yes, that would be nice if it happened.

\N<Yuia>It will happen, the first step is to believe that it will.
If we don't believe in it, then who will?

\N<Yuia>...I will definitely protect you all. And I will make sure
to bring you happiness.

I wonder if I can share the same smile as the person I love
right now. I hope I'm not causing them any anxiety.
I'm sure... I'll fall into hell.

But even so, I will definitely push Yuia-sama and this child
up from the depths of hell to the surface.

How ridiculous I am... knowing full well that such excuses
are nothing but a way to escape responsibility.

Yet... at that time, such foolish self-defense was... all I
could muster.
